title: Grateful Dead Live at Cal Expo on 1991-05-03
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi CR-7A) > Tascam DA-3000 (DSF 1-bit/5.6 MHz) >dBpoweramp > Adobe Audition CC2015 > Samplitude Pro X3 Suite > FLAC/24
description:
Set 1

Bertha-> Greatest Story Ever Told, West L.A. Fadeaway, Queen Jane Approximately, Jack A Roe, It's All Over Now, Tennessee Jed, Let It Grow

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Estimated Prophet-> He's Gone-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> All Along The Watchtower-> Stella Blue-> Turn On Your Love Light, E: U.S. Blues

reviews.review_text:
20th Birthday Spent the day with good friends and the band contributed to a memorable birthday. 

Went to 5/4, but friends did not have tickets. They went to Chico to party and were to pick me up the next day. My buddy who was driving left me hangin' but it's all OK because I stole his girlfriend and we are still married all these years later. AND Keith is still my friend. 

Twentieth birthday, saw the Grateful Dead and met my soul-mate. Kind of a pivotal weekend in my life.
Thank you Have a nice day. 😊
